history.content: You can read Nick Weaver's post from a while ago to get a better idea. Your ability to enroll in 70 is likely to be determined by the semester you enrolled at Berkeley and if you listed CS as an intended major on your undergrad application, not your calCentral enrollment time.

Hello! 

I'm not sure if this question has been asked before and I missed it, but I've heard from a lot of people that the cs70 class size has been reduced and whether or not we'll be able to declare depends on our enrollment time slot. I'm not entirely sure if this information is credible (because frankly, it doesn't make much sense to me), so could someone confirm or deny this? 

Additionally, if anyone could share any updates on how the funding crisis is going to affect students who didn't indicate cs on their application it would be much appreciated! 

Thanks
